This paper discusses the use of label smoothing in neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning and deep learning. The paper specifically mentions its use in image classification, language translation, and speech recognition, which are all subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the effect of label smoothing on model calibration and knowledge distillation, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
